children.name: hash_map
children.brief: Implemented size:4096 bytes = (2 words per bank) x (2048 bytes per word) | Memory Usage:1024 RAMs | Number of banks:1 | Bank width (word size):2048 bytes | Bank depth:2 words | Number of replicates:1 | Number of private copies:1 | RAM Mode:True dual-port | Pump configuration:Single-pumped | User defined attributes:memory(BLOCK_RAM)

details.Implemented size: 4096 bytes = (2 words per bank) x (2048 bytes per word)

Additional information.text: Shallow memory implemented in RAMs instead of MLABs because MLABs cannot be configured in true dual-port mode.
RAM usage is increased from 512 RAMs to 1024 RAMs because the width of individual RAM blocks in true dual-port mode is limited to 20 bits.
In each private copy:</br>  Variable 'hash_map' occupies memory words [0-1] and has 1 array element split across 1 memory words.
